              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Sixteen telescopes of the High",
                "Resolution Array HiRA measured the energies and",
                "angles of the deuterons. Telescopes were located 35",
                "cm from the target and covered polar angles of 4deg -",
                "45deg in the laboratory frame. Each telescope",
                "contained one 65 mu-m thick dE and one 1500 mu-m",
                "thick E silicon strip detector that were backed by",
                "four 3.9cm thick CsI(Tl) crystals."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The HiRA, MCP and reaction targets were",
                "placed in a scattering chamber in front of the S800",
                "spectrometer, which detected the 55Ni residues."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between 55Ni residues and",
                "            deuterons was required."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Secondary 56Ni beam was produced by fragmentation of",
                "140 MeV/A primary beam of 58Ni on a 1269 mg/cm2",
                "beryllium production target. The A1900 fragment",
                "separator filtered 56Ni nuclei from the resulting",
                "fragmentation products to a purity of 72% and",
                "degraded their energies to 37 MeV/nucleon."
              ]
            }
